{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H3SUCdYbUfGGhNHfLQkrAn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the findings:\n\n## Summary of Web UI Codebase Exploration\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's everything you need to know about the web UI architecture:\n\n### 1. **Web UI Code Location**\n- **Main handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,438 lines)\n- **Templates**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout template\n  - `project_detail.html` - Project detail page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Run detail page\n  - `projects.html` - Projects overview page\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n- **Static assets**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 2. **Project Detail Page Architecture**\n\n**Handler**: `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 942-976)\n- Route: `GET /projects/{name}`\n- Loads project info via API endpoints\n- Passes basic data to template: label, dir, recentRuns, containerCount\n\n**Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- Structure:\n  - Project info panel (Docker image, version, prompt files)\n  - Workflow panel with tabs and DAG visualization\n  - Step drawer for detailed step information\n- Uses vanilla JavaScript (no framework)\n- Has CSS-defined tab UI at `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` lines 434-455\n\n**Key Features Currently Implemented**:\n- Tab bar for multiple workflows (lines 105-114 of project_detail.html)\n- SVG DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) visualization (lines 164-202)\n- Step drawer for viewing step configuration (lines 205-242)\n- Workflow metadata display in grid layout\n\n### 3. **Current Workflow Display**\n\nThe project detail page currently shows **container workflows only**:\n\n**API Endpoint**: `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1097-1171)\n- Route: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- **Explicitly skips host.cloche**: Line 1132 filters out `host.cloche`\n- Iterates through `.cloche/*.cloche` files (excluding `host.cloche`)\n- Uses `dsl.ParseForContainer()` to parse container workflows only\n- Returns JSON array of workflows with: name, file, steps, wires, entry_step\n\n**Workflow Structure in API Response**:\n```go\ntype apiWorkflow struct {\n    Name      string       `json:\"name\"`\n    File      string       `json:\"file\"`\n    Steps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n    Wires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n    EntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Host Workflows vs Container Workflows**\n\n**LocationHost (host.cloche)**:\n- Runs on the host machine (not in a container)\n- Located in `.cloche/host.cloche`\n- Can dispatch container workflow runs as child runs\n- Parsed with `dsl.ParseAllForHost()` which returns `map[string]*domain.Workflow` (multiple workflows per file)\n- Uses `workflow_name` step type to invoke container workflows\n- Can contain multiple named workflows (e.g., \"main\", \"list-tasks\", \"finalize\")\n- Example at `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` with steps like `ready-tasks`, `claim-task`, `develop`, `merge`, `cleanup`\n\n**LocationContainer (develop.cloche, build.cloche, etc.)**:\n- Runs inside Docker containers\n- All `.cloche/*.cloche` files except `host.cloche`\n- Parsed with `dsl.ParseForContainer()` which returns single `*domain.Workflow`\n- Can only have `agent`, `script`, `workflow` step types\n- `workflow_name` steps are explicitly forbidden in container workflows (validation in `workflow.go` lines 233-241)\n\n**Key Distinction in Code**:\n- Line 1132 in handler.go: `e.Name() == \"host.cloche\"` explicitly excludes host workflows\n- Domain types show: `IsHost bool` in Run struct (line 45 of run.go)\n- API response: `is_host` field distinguishes host vs container runs\n- Runs display: Lines 31 & 36 of runs.html show `{{if .IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}`\n\n### 5. **Existing Tab UI Patterns**\n\nThe codebase already has a working tab UI system:\n\n**CSS** (`style.css` lines 434-455):\n```css\n.tab-bar { display: flex; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.tab-btn { padding: 0.4rem 1rem; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; }\n.tab-btn.tab-active { color: var(--link); border-bottom-color: var(--link); }\n```\n\n**JavaScript Implementation** (project_detail.html lines 106-114):\n```javascript\nif (workflowsData.length > 1) {\n    var html = '';\n    workflowsData.forEach(function(wf, i) {\n        html += '<button class=\"tab-btn' + (i === 0 ? ' tab-active' : '') + '\" onclick=\"showWorkflow(' + i + ')\">' + wf.name + '</button>';\n    });\n    tabs.innerHTML = html;\n}\n```\n\n**Tab Toggle Function** (showWorkflow, lines 117-203):\n- Updates active tab styling\n- Renders the appropriate workflow DAG\n- Maintains tab state in JavaScript\n\n### 6. **Workflow Type Definition**\n\n**Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` lines 135-143):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // host or container\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire\n    Collects  []Collect\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**WorkflowLocation Constants** (lines 22-33):\n```go\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"\n)\n```\n\n### 7. **Key API Endpoints**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `GET /projects/{name}` | HTML | Renders project detail page |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` | JSON | Project metadata (Docker image, version, prompt files) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` | JSON | Lists all **container** workflows (excludes host.cloche) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | Text | Step content (prompt/script/command) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | Text | Git diff for prompt file changes |\n\n### 8. **Related Data Structures**\n\n**Step Definition** (workflow.go lines 35-40):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // agent, script, workflow\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Run Type** (run.go lines 31-47):\n- Contains: `IsHost bool`, `ParentRunID string`\n- Host runs can have child runs (container runs they dispatched)\n- Child runs link back to parent via `ParentRunID`\n\n**Execution Tracking**:\n- `StepExecution` records each step's start/end/result\n- Stored in `CaptureStore` (ports interface)\n- Displayed in run detail page's steps table\n\n### 9. **Static Assets**\n\n**CSS file**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n- Complete styling for all UI components\n- Color scheme with CSS variables\n- Responsive design\n- Includes styling for: badges, tabs, drawers, DAGs, panels, tables, forms\n- Dark mode support via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`\n\n### 10. **Current Limitations/Gaps**\n\n- **Host workflows not visible**: The API endpoint explicitly skips `host.cloche` (line 1132)\n- **Host workflow visualization missing**: No UI to display the host workflow structure\n- **Single workflow type in project_detail**: The tab system is built for container workflows only\n- **No host-specific handling**: No separate section or visualization for host workflows\n\nThis is the complete state of the web UI codebase. The architecture is well-structured and ready for enhancement to include host workflow visualization."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abb5b7df3e70851b7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65339\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 48548</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0fcc3bc-5e1e-4706-af96-922d8476da68","uuid":"80a52a7b-d92b-4ff9-9922-5319aa1ba323","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the web UI codebase for this project. I need to understand:\n\n1. Where the web UI code lives (look for HTML templates, handlers, static files)\n2. How the Project detail page currently works - find the template and handler\n3. How workflows are currently displayed on the Project detail page\n4. How host workflows (.cloche/host.cloche) differ from container workflows (.cloche/develop.cloche)\n5. Any existing tab UI patterns in the codebase\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- Web UI templates (*.html, *.templ, *.tmpl)\n- Web handlers/routes\n- Project detail page specifically\n- Workflow-related types and how they're loaded\n- Host workflow types vs container workflow types\n\nBe very thorough - check all relevant directories.","agentId":"abb5b7df3e70851b7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the findings:\n\n## Summary of Web UI Codebase Exploration\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's everything you need to know about the web UI architecture:\n\n### 1. **Web UI Code Location**\n- **Main handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,438 lines)\n- **Templates**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout template\n  - `project_detail.html` - Project detail page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Run detail page\n  - `projects.html` - Projects overview page\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n- **Static assets**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 2. **Project Detail Page Architecture**\n\n**Handler**: `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 942-976)\n- Route: `GET /projects/{name}`\n- Loads project info via API endpoints\n- Passes basic data to template: label, dir, recentRuns, containerCount\n\n**Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- Structure:\n  - Project info panel (Docker image, version, prompt files)\n  - Workflow panel with tabs and DAG visualization\n  - Step drawer for detailed step information\n- Uses vanilla JavaScript (no framework)\n- Has CSS-defined tab UI at `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` lines 434-455\n\n**Key Features Currently Implemented**:\n- Tab bar for multiple workflows (lines 105-114 of project_detail.html)\n- SVG DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) visualization (lines 164-202)\n- Step drawer for viewing step configuration (lines 205-242)\n- Workflow metadata display in grid layout\n\n### 3. **Current Workflow Display**\n\nThe project detail page currently shows **container workflows only**:\n\n**API Endpoint**: `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1097-1171)\n- Route: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- **Explicitly skips host.cloche**: Line 1132 filters out `host.cloche`\n- Iterates through `.cloche/*.cloche` files (excluding `host.cloche`)\n- Uses `dsl.ParseForContainer()` to parse container workflows only\n- Returns JSON array of workflows with: name, file, steps, wires, entry_step\n\n**Workflow Structure in API Response**:\n```go\ntype apiWorkflow struct {\n    Name      string       `json:\"name\"`\n    File      string       `json:\"file\"`\n    Steps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n    Wires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n    EntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Host Workflows vs Container Workflows**\n\n**LocationHost (host.cloche)**:\n- Runs on the host machine (not in a container)\n- Located in `.cloche/host.cloche`\n- Can dispatch container workflow runs as child runs\n- Parsed with `dsl.ParseAllForHost()` which returns `map[string]*domain.Workflow` (multiple workflows per file)\n- Uses `workflow_name` step type to invoke container workflows\n- Can contain multiple named workflows (e.g., \"main\", \"list-tasks\", \"finalize\")\n- Example at `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` with steps like `ready-tasks`, `claim-task`, `develop`, `merge`, `cleanup`\n\n**LocationContainer (develop.cloche, build.cloche, etc.)**:\n- Runs inside Docker containers\n- All `.cloche/*.cloche` files except `host.cloche`\n- Parsed with `dsl.ParseForContainer()` which returns single `*domain.Workflow`\n- Can only have `agent`, `script`, `workflow` step types\n- `workflow_name` steps are explicitly forbidden in container workflows (validation in `workflow.go` lines 233-241)\n\n**Key Distinction in Code**:\n- Line 1132 in handler.go: `e.Name() == \"host.cloche\"` explicitly excludes host workflows\n- Domain types show: `IsHost bool` in Run struct (line 45 of run.go)\n- API response: `is_host` field distinguishes host vs container runs\n- Runs display: Lines 31 & 36 of runs.html show `{{if .IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}`\n\n### 5. **Existing Tab UI Patterns**\n\nThe codebase already has a working tab UI system:\n\n**CSS** (`style.css` lines 434-455):\n```css\n.tab-bar { display: flex; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.tab-btn { padding: 0.4rem 1rem; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; }\n.tab-btn.tab-active { color: var(--link); border-bottom-color: var(--link); }\n```\n\n**JavaScript Implementation** (project_detail.html lines 106-114):\n```javascript\nif (workflowsData.length > 1) {\n    var html = '';\n    workflowsData.forEach(function(wf, i) {\n        html += '<button class=\"tab-btn' + (i === 0 ? ' tab-active' : '') + '\" onclick=\"showWorkflow(' + i + ')\">' + wf.name + '</button>';\n    });\n    tabs.innerHTML = html;\n}\n```\n\n**Tab Toggle Function** (showWorkflow, lines 117-203):\n- Updates active tab styling\n- Renders the appropriate workflow DAG\n- Maintains tab state in JavaScript\n\n### 6. **Workflow Type Definition**\n\n**Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` lines 135-143):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // host or container\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire\n    Collects  []Collect\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**WorkflowLocation Constants** (lines 22-33):\n```go\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"\n)\n```\n\n### 7. **Key API Endpoints**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `GET /projects/{name}` | HTML | Renders project detail page |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` | JSON | Project metadata (Docker image, version, prompt files) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` | JSON | Lists all **container** workflows (excludes host.cloche) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | Text | Step content (prompt/script/command) |\n| `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | Text | Git diff for prompt file changes |\n\n### 8. **Related Data Structures**\n\n**Step Definition** (workflow.go lines 35-40):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // agent, script, workflow\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Run Type** (run.go lines 31-47):\n- Contains: `IsHost bool`, `ParentRunID string`\n- Host runs can have child runs (container runs they dispatched)\n- Child runs link back to parent via `ParentRunID`\n\n**Execution Tracking**:\n- `StepExecution` records each step's start/end/result\n- Stored in `CaptureStore` (ports interface)\n- Displayed in run detail page's steps table\n\n### 9. **Static Assets**\n\n**CSS file**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n- Complete styling for all UI components\n- Color scheme with CSS variables\n- Responsive design\n- Includes styling for: badges, tabs, drawers, DAGs, panels, tables, forms\n- Dark mode support via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`\n\n### 10. **Current Limitations/Gaps**\n\n- **Host workflows not visible**: The API endpoint explicitly skips `host.cloche` (line 1132)\n- **Host workflow visualization missing**: No UI to display the host workflow structure\n- **Single workflow type in project_detail**: The tab system is built for container workflows only\n- **No host-specific handling**: No separate section or visualization for host workflows\n\nThis is the complete state of the web UI codebase. The architecture is well-structured and ready for enhancement to include host workflow visualization."}],"totalDurationMs":48548,"totalTokens":65339,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1522,"cache_read_input_tokens":61711,"output_tokens":2100,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1522},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
