{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UPoSiNRnEJArJL6Dn4ZqR9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis: Domain Types and Workflow-Related Code\n\n### 1. **Workflow Type Structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`)\n\nThe `Workflow` struct is the central domain type with the following fields:\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string                // Workflow name (e.g., \"develop\", \"main\")\n    Location  WorkflowLocation      // host or container\n    Steps     map[string]*Step      // Step definitions by name\n    Wiring    []Wire                // Connections between steps\n    Collects  []Collect             // Multi-step synchronization rules\n    EntryStep string                // Initial step name\n    Config    map[string]string     // Workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **Host vs Container Workflows (Type System Distinction)**\n\nThere is a clear distinction in the type system via the `WorkflowLocation` enum:\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\n\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"  // Workflows in *.cloche files\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"       // Only in host.cloche\n)\n```\n\n**Key Differences:**\n- **Container workflows** (`LocationContainer`): Allow `StepTypeAgent` and `StepTypeScript` steps only\n- **Host workflows** (`LocationHost`): Allow all step types including `StepTypeWorkflow`\n- The validation is enforced in `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` (lines 231-242), which rejects `workflow_name` steps in container workflows\n\n**Location is set at parse time:**\n- `ParseForContainer()` sets `location = \"container\"`\n- `ParseForHost()` / `ParseAllForHost()` sets `location = \"host\"`\n- Plain `Parse()` with no option leaves location empty (no validation)\n\n### 3. **Step Types**\n\n```go\ntype StepType string\n\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    StepType = \"agent\"     // Agent-based (uses \"prompt\")\n    StepTypeScript   StepType = \"script\"    // Shell script (uses \"run\")\n    StepTypeWorkflow StepType = \"workflow\"  // Container workflow dispatch (uses \"workflow_name\")\n)\n```\n\nStep type is inferred from config during parsing (lines 224-253):\n- If `prompt` config key exists → `StepTypeAgent`\n- If `run` config key exists → `StepTypeScript`\n- If `workflow_name` config key exists → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host only)\n\n### 4. **Workflow Loading/Parsing Code**\n\n**Parser Location:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\nThree main parsing functions:\n\n1. **`Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 28)\n   - Generic parser that creates a Workflow with optional location set\n\n2. **`ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 39)\n   - Parses a single host workflow (used by web/projects)\n   - Sets `location = LocationHost`\n   - Calls `Parse()` with `WithLocation(domain.LocationHost)`\n\n3. **`ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 45)\n   - Parses multiple workflows from host.cloche file\n   - Returns `map[string]*Workflow` indexed by workflow name\n   - Used by `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` to load and execute host workflows\n\n4. **`ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 70)\n   - Parses container workflows (*.cloche files other than host.cloche)\n   - Sets `location = LocationContainer`\n   - Validates that no `workflow_name` steps are present\n\n### 5. **Project Detail Page Workflow Loading**\n\n**Handler:** `handleAPIWorkflows()` in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1097-1171)\n\nThis handler loads and serves workflow definitions for the project detail page:\n\n1. **Discovery:** Reads `.cloche/` directory\n2. **Filtering:** Skips `host.cloche` and directories\n3. **Parsing:** For each `*.cloche` file:\n   - Calls `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n   - Extracts step definitions and wiring\n4. **Response:** Returns JSON array of `apiWorkflow` structs with:\n   - `name`: Workflow name\n   - `file`: File path (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`)\n   - `steps`: Step definitions with type, results, config\n   - `wires`: Wire connections (from, result, to)\n   - `entry_step`: Entry step name\n\n**Note:** `host.cloche` is explicitly excluded (line 1132) because it contains orchestration logic, not container workflow definitions.\n\n### 6. **Related Port Interfaces**\n\n**`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`:**\n- `RunStore.ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)` — Returns project directories\n- `RunStore.ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` — Gets runs for a project\n\n**`/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`:**\n- `AgentAdapter` — Executes a single agent step\n- Domain-independent; various implementations (Claude Code, generic, etc.)\n\n### 7. **Run Type with Location Awareness**\n\n**`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID          string\n    WorkflowName string\n    State       RunState\n    IsHost      bool      // true for host workflow runs vs container runs\n    ParentRunID string    // ID of parent (host) run if this is a child\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\nThe run type tracks whether it's a host or container run, enabling parent-child run relationships when host workflows dispatch container workflows.\n\n### 8. **Workflow Execution**\n\n**Host Runner:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `Runner.RunNamed()` loads `host.cloche` via `dsl.ParseAllForHost()`\n- Selects named workflow from the returned map\n- Executes via the engine with `Executor` (host step executor)\n\n**Engine:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n- Generic workflow execution engine\n- Works with any `StepExecutor` implementation\n- Handles wiring, fan-out, collect clauses\n\n### 9. **Summary of Key Files**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | `Workflow`, `WorkflowLocation`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Collect` types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | `Run` type with `IsHost`, `ParentRunID` fields |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | DSL parsing: `Parse`, `ParseForHost`, `ParseForContainer`, `ParseAllForHost` |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow runner; uses `ParseAllForHost()` to load workflows |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | `handleAPIWorkflows()` loads container workflows for project detail page (uses `ParseForContainer()`) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Generic workflow execution engine |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step executor; handles script, workflow, and agent steps |\n\nThe architecture cleanly separates host orchestration (multi-step task dispatch) from container execution (autonomous agent workflows) through the `WorkflowLocation` type system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1cefe0011f86b305 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65713\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 63112</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0fcc3bc-5e1e-4706-af96-922d8476da68","uuid":"7637de96-1ae4-4488-ba66-bef66145185c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the domain types and workflow-related code in this Go project. I need to understand:\n\n1. The Workflow type in internal/domain/ - what fields does it have?\n2. Is there a distinction between \"host\" workflows and \"container/agent\" workflows in the type system?\n3. How are workflows loaded/parsed? Look for workflow loading functions.\n4. How does the project detail page handler load workflows?\n5. Look at internal/domain/, internal/ports/, and any web-related adapters\n\nSearch for:\n- Workflow struct definitions\n- Host workflow vs container workflow distinctions\n- Workflow file loading/parsing code\n- Any \"project\" related types\n\nBe very thorough.","agentId":"a1cefe0011f86b305","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis: Domain Types and Workflow-Related Code\n\n### 1. **Workflow Type Structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`)\n\nThe `Workflow` struct is the central domain type with the following fields:\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string                // Workflow name (e.g., \"develop\", \"main\")\n    Location  WorkflowLocation      // host or container\n    Steps     map[string]*Step      // Step definitions by name\n    Wiring    []Wire                // Connections between steps\n    Collects  []Collect             // Multi-step synchronization rules\n    EntryStep string                // Initial step name\n    Config    map[string]string     // Workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **Host vs Container Workflows (Type System Distinction)**\n\nThere is a clear distinction in the type system via the `WorkflowLocation` enum:\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\n\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"  // Workflows in *.cloche files\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"       // Only in host.cloche\n)\n```\n\n**Key Differences:**\n- **Container workflows** (`LocationContainer`): Allow `StepTypeAgent` and `StepTypeScript` steps only\n- **Host workflows** (`LocationHost`): Allow all step types including `StepTypeWorkflow`\n- The validation is enforced in `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` (lines 231-242), which rejects `workflow_name` steps in container workflows\n\n**Location is set at parse time:**\n- `ParseForContainer()` sets `location = \"container\"`\n- `ParseForHost()` / `ParseAllForHost()` sets `location = \"host\"`\n- Plain `Parse()` with no option leaves location empty (no validation)\n\n### 3. **Step Types**\n\n```go\ntype StepType string\n\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    StepType = \"agent\"     // Agent-based (uses \"prompt\")\n    StepTypeScript   StepType = \"script\"    // Shell script (uses \"run\")\n    StepTypeWorkflow StepType = \"workflow\"  // Container workflow dispatch (uses \"workflow_name\")\n)\n```\n\nStep type is inferred from config during parsing (lines 224-253):\n- If `prompt` config key exists → `StepTypeAgent`\n- If `run` config key exists → `StepTypeScript`\n- If `workflow_name` config key exists → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host only)\n\n### 4. **Workflow Loading/Parsing Code**\n\n**Parser Location:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\nThree main parsing functions:\n\n1. **`Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 28)\n   - Generic parser that creates a Workflow with optional location set\n\n2. **`ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 39)\n   - Parses a single host workflow (used by web/projects)\n   - Sets `location = LocationHost`\n   - Calls `Parse()` with `WithLocation(domain.LocationHost)`\n\n3. **`ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 45)\n   - Parses multiple workflows from host.cloche file\n   - Returns `map[string]*Workflow` indexed by workflow name\n   - Used by `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` to load and execute host workflows\n\n4. **`ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)`** (line 70)\n   - Parses container workflows (*.cloche files other than host.cloche)\n   - Sets `location = LocationContainer`\n   - Validates that no `workflow_name` steps are present\n\n### 5. **Project Detail Page Workflow Loading**\n\n**Handler:** `handleAPIWorkflows()` in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1097-1171)\n\nThis handler loads and serves workflow definitions for the project detail page:\n\n1. **Discovery:** Reads `.cloche/` directory\n2. **Filtering:** Skips `host.cloche` and directories\n3. **Parsing:** For each `*.cloche` file:\n   - Calls `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n   - Extracts step definitions and wiring\n4. **Response:** Returns JSON array of `apiWorkflow` structs with:\n   - `name`: Workflow name\n   - `file`: File path (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`)\n   - `steps`: Step definitions with type, results, config\n   - `wires`: Wire connections (from, result, to)\n   - `entry_step`: Entry step name\n\n**Note:** `host.cloche` is explicitly excluded (line 1132) because it contains orchestration logic, not container workflow definitions.\n\n### 6. **Related Port Interfaces**\n\n**`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`:**\n- `RunStore.ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)` — Returns project directories\n- `RunStore.ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` — Gets runs for a project\n\n**`/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`:**\n- `AgentAdapter` — Executes a single agent step\n- Domain-independent; various implementations (Claude Code, generic, etc.)\n\n### 7. **Run Type with Location Awareness**\n\n**`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID          string\n    WorkflowName string\n    State       RunState\n    IsHost      bool      // true for host workflow runs vs container runs\n    ParentRunID string    // ID of parent (host) run if this is a child\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\nThe run type tracks whether it's a host or container run, enabling parent-child run relationships when host workflows dispatch container workflows.\n\n### 8. **Workflow Execution**\n\n**Host Runner:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `Runner.RunNamed()` loads `host.cloche` via `dsl.ParseAllForHost()`\n- Selects named workflow from the returned map\n- Executes via the engine with `Executor` (host step executor)\n\n**Engine:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n- Generic workflow execution engine\n- Works with any `StepExecutor` implementation\n- Handles wiring, fan-out, collect clauses\n\n### 9. **Summary of Key Files**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | `Workflow`, `WorkflowLocation`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Collect` types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | `Run` type with `IsHost`, `ParentRunID` fields |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | DSL parsing: `Parse`, `ParseForHost`, `ParseForContainer`, `ParseAllForHost` |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow runner; uses `ParseAllForHost()` to load workflows |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | `handleAPIWorkflows()` loads container workflows for project detail page (uses `ParseForContainer()`) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Generic workflow execution engine |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step executor; handles script, workflow, and agent steps |\n\nThe architecture cleanly separates host orchestration (multi-step task dispatch) from container execution (autonomous agent workflows) through the `WorkflowLocation` type system."}],"totalDurationMs":63112,"totalTokens":65713,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":398,"cache_read_input_tokens":63445,"output_tokens":1865,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":398},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
